🐣 Keep your Easter eggs forever!
Blow out the yolk and whites so your eggs don’t spoil.

Here’s how:
	•	Gently poke a small hole at the top and a slightly larger hole at the bottom of the egg.
	•	Use a needle or skewer to stir the inside and break up the yolk.
	•	Blow through the top hole until the egg is completely empty.
	•	Rinse the shell with water and let it dry.
	•	Now you’re ready to decorate and enjoy your eggs for years to come!

#eastereggs #blowouteggs #momhack

💡 If your makeup isn’t blending, looking smooth, or giving you the coverage you want… the real problem might be your skincare—not your makeup!

❌ Myth #1: If foundation looks patchy, just blend harder.
✔️ Truth: Dehydrated skin causes foundation to cling to dry spots. Fix it with weekly exfoliation and daily hydration, not more blending.

❌ Myth #2: Thick concealer is the best way to cover dark circles.
✔️ Truth: A lightweight, hydrating formula works better, but the real game-changer? Color correction! Using the right color corrector lets you achieve better coverage with less product—no cakiness, no creasing.

❌ Myth #3: Large pores need more primer.
✔️ Truth: Hydration + exfoliation minimizes the appearance of pores over time. While primer offers a temporary fix, a solid skincare routine will give you smoother skin that looks flawless even without makeup!

💬 Have you tried fixing your makeup problems with better skincare? If not, I’d love to help! Let me know what the problem is and let’s work on it together!☺️
